## Alterations Implemented within "EVE" Module (in order of implementation.):  



**a.) Addition Of Auxiliary Channels:**   - The core idea revolves around introducing auxiliary channels alongside max pooling operations using a custom `MinPool` module (`MiniPOOL`) designed specificallyfor minpooling operation followed immediately after Max Pooling layers.(This technique boosts information flow between spatial dimensions).





 **b)** Concatenation With Identity Mapping**: After creating two separate minipools via 'MIN POOL', their outputs are concatenated along channel dimension prior entering subsequent convolutional layer.`Identity mapping`, achieved simplyby adding identical copiesof inputs as additionalchannels, helps preserve high frequency components lost during downsampling processes like MAXPooling.




   <strong>c.** Nonlinearities Within Mini pool Layer :</strong> Instead relying solely on negative scaling factor (-X )within ``MAX POOL``’S reduction formula,“ MINPooL” incorporates non linearity introducedvia exponential decay factors applied directly onto features extracted from X before applying maximum subtraction.<br>







﻿ ## Conclusion & Future Directions	<p/> Overall these modifications enhance feature extraction capabilities while preserving valuablehighfrequencyinformation embedded deepWithininput tensors—leadingto improvedperformanceon tasks involving object detection or semantic segmentationwhere precise localizationand classification is paramount

