## Proposed Modifications (with Explanation)**




### Padding Technique ("PadNumY") Enhancement






* **Objective**: Increase receptive field of convolution layer without significantly impacting parameter count nor introducing additional bias due excessive padding applied uniformly across all dimensions like traditional `padding` method does.. This technique utilizes asymmetric zero paddings tailored specifically per kernel size (`ks`) instead uniform paddling adopted previously via 'K' argument during conv operation implementation.' The asymmetry introduces variable number pads depending upon fractional multiples derived from " k" value resulting into nonuniform spatial expansion along channels leading improved feature extraction capabilities at lower costs than conventional symmetric padded layers,. Additionally, it minimizes information loss arising out redundant copies introduced when employing large strides combined symmetricalpaddding schemes commonly employed today.' 





