## Modifications Proposed - "DW" Class Enhancement



**I.) Padding Calculation:**  Currently `padding` per side (`pad_par_sides`) depends on half of ``ks`` minus one (rounded down). This results inaccurate padding when 'kw', which governs overall width expansion due its inclusion within stride calculations later during network construction ("dilated convolution"). To rectify that issue; instead calculating based off roundeddown(`half*Ks`), calculate it using ceiling operation applied upon halved value ('ceil').   This ensures exact number pads from both sides resulting balanced dilation across all layers while preserving output size consistency.




 **II)** Group Convolution Implementation**: The existing implementation uses group convolutions incorrectly – currently grouping channels into blocks equal tot he channel count (“groups” parameter set erroneously high.). Instead, evenly distribute them over multiple sets according their cardinality (‘group’ attribute should match desired #sets not total#channels ).







---





